<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD INSPECTION -
        PRESSURE CHECK CYLINDER HEAD
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="4">
        <title>PRESSURE CHECK CYLINDER HEAD</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pressure testing the cylinder head will reveal cracks in ports or nozzle sleeve leakage
                which cannot be observed using dye penetrant. Pressure-test the cylinder head as follows:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Reinstall injection nozzles before pressure testing.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Nozzle clamping seals the nozzle sleeve at the bottom of the bore in the head. Good nozzle
                            sleeves will be condemned needlessly if nozzles are not installed prior to pressure testing.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the valves, using a valve spring compressor. Refer to "
                    <emph type="bold">CYLINDER HEAD RECONDITIONING</emph>", in this section for valve removal
                    instructions.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050418" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1711" filename="../figeg1/EG1711.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.18.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Purple Line/Crack</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Pressure test the cylinder head using the Cylinder Head Pressure Test Plate Kit (
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE4289-1A</emph>
                    Hardware and Regulator and
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE4289-2A</emph>
                    Plate. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050419">4.19</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Fasten the pressure plate and head gasket to the cylinder head gasket surface using the
                    twenty-four (24) mounting bolts and nuts supplied with the kit. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050420">4.20</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove thermostat and install air regulator. Secure to cylinder head with two (2)
                    mounting bolts.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the pipe plug next to the thermostat opening. Fill cylinder head with hot water
                    and reinstall pipe plug. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050421">4.21</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install a hose fitting to the cylinder head at the removed plug. Apply 18-20 psi
                    (124-138 kPa) air pressure and visually inspect for leaks at the:
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Nozzle sleeves</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Ports</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Upper deck</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Lower deck</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If leakage is observed at any port or the upper and lower deck, REPLACE THE CYLINDER HEAD.
                            If nozzle sleeve leakage is observed, follow the procedures under "CYLINDER HEAD
                            RECONDITIONING".
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef1050419" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3021" filename="../figeg3/EG3021.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.19.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Pressure Test Plate</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Air Regulator</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Pressure Test Plate Mounting Bolts (24)</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050420" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3022" filename="../figeg3/EG3022.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.20.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Cylinder Head</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Pressure Test Plate</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Pressure Test Plate Mounting Bolts</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050421" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3023" filename="../figeg3/EG3023.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.21.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Cylinder Head</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Air Regulator</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Air Hose</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
